{
  "texts": [
    "In rare cases where the differences were greater, it appeared that gpt-4o-mini got confused in sentiment scoring of long text reviews.",
    "Supply-Word-4o did not have this issue as gpt-4o is naturally better at understanding sentiment.",
    "However, scoring PDT data at scale would not be cost effective with gpt-4o.",
    "Further, Supply-Word-4o is somewhat of an apples to oranges comparison because it compares the target scores of synthetic text generated by gpt-4o-mini (with its own understanding of sentiment) with evaluated scores produced by gpt-4o (with a slightly different understanding of sentiment).",
    "While gpt-4o handled the cases where gpt-4o-mini got confused, there were other medium differences across the dataset, presumably because the two models have a slightly different understanding of sentiment.Table IV shows the statistical data for the three approaches."
  ]
}